This web site is about living and working in orbit; not just for few months, but on evolutionary time scales; where Life evolves inside of hundreds of thousands, if not millions, of kilometer-scale, artificial, orbital habitats. Earth-based Life's establishment of these settlements would be an evolutionary event of a magnitude similar to, if not greater than, ocean-based Life's colonization of land half a billion years ago.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Space settlement site by Mike Combs<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/CapeCanaveral/Lab/9917/settle.htm">www.geocities.com/CapeCanaveral/Lab/9917/settle.htm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Space settlement is a unique concept for colonization beyond the Earth.  While most thinking regarding the expansion of the human race outward into space has focused on the colonization of the surfaces of other planets, the space settlement concept suggests that planetary surfaces may not be the best location for extraterrestrial colonies.  Artificial, closed-ecology habitats in free orbit would seem to have many advantages over any planetary home (Earth included).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=johnfraz>John Fraz</A> at: 10/31/03 12:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cotopaxi@nuclearspace>cotopaxi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/31/03 2:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=963.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/16.gif" align=absmiddle>  spinner space </span><hr size=1> John you're absolutely right...look, my post on the subject was clouded a bit by frustration when I read fantastic Sci-fi type machinations and the people that subscribe to them as &quot;gospel truth&quot;. Meanwhile back at &quot;Reality Ranch&quot; nothing ever gets done. This known for an amateur space cadet like me. If you follow the c-span link <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.c-span.org/VideoArchives.asp?z1=&amp;PopupMenu_Name=Science/Technology&amp;CatCodePairs=Issue,ST;" target="top">c-span.org VideoArchives</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> or U.S. senate link <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.senate.gov/~commerce/hearings/witnesslist.cfm?i